### Design Decisions

- Auto-detection requires zero config changes for users who set up id-token: write
- Explicit oidc: true is for migration scenarios or explicit enforcement
- Token still stored when oidc: true + NPM_TOKEN set (used for getLatestVersion on private packages)
- checkPackageName without token in OIDC mode: warn and skip (not error) to avoid blocking publish
- Provenance: auto-generated by npm when using OIDC on public repos; no config option needed
- Yarn fallback: not allowed in OIDC mode (OIDC is npm-specific)
